<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL; NO. 4 ARKANSAS GETS PAST LSU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arkansas' Clint McDaniel made a free throw with 39 seconds left to break the 
game's final tie and Louisiana State's Jamie Brandon missed two shots in the 
final seconds as the fourth-ranked Razorbacks slipped by the Tigers, 84-83, 
Tuesday night at Fayetteville, Ark. 
</P>
<P>
 McDaniel, who was fouled after a steal near midcourt, missed the second of his 
two free throws. Brandon's 12-footer hit the rim, but the Tigers, 7-4 overall 
and 1-2 in the Southeastern Conference, got the rebound and he missed again 
from about the same distance. 
</P>
<P>
 Dwight Stewart added 17 points for Arkansas (11-1, 2-1) and Scotty Thurman had 
15. Ronnie Henderson led LSU with 25 points. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 11 Indiana 89, Iowa 75 -- Brian Evans, showing no ill effects of a 
separated shoulder, scored a career-high 21 points and Todd Lindeman gave 
Indiana a second-half lift at Iowa City, Iowa. 
</P>
<P>
 Damon Bailey and Pat Graham each scored 20 points for the Hoosiers (9-2, 2-0 
Big Ten), who have won five in a row over Iowa (6-6, 0-3).  
</P>
<P>
 No. 13 Temple 76, Penn 65 -- Aaron McKie scored 24 points and Eddie Jones 
added 22 as Temple rallied in the final eight minutes at Philadelphia to end 
the Quakers' eight-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Trailing, 51-50, with 7:55 to play, Temple (8-2) outscored Penn, 15-3, to take 
a 65-54 lead with 2:20 left and went on to its 13th consecutive victory over 
the Quakers (9-2). OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Dickie Simpkins scored 23 points, including 14 in the first half, and Michael 
Smith added 19 points to lead Providence (9-2, 3-1) to an 86-72 Big East 
Conference victory over Rhode Island (5-5, 2-3) at Providence, R.I. . . . Dan 
Cross stole an inbounds pass with 23 seconds to play and then made two free 
throws to lift Florida (12-2) to a 69-64 victory over South Florida (8-5) at 
St. Petersburg, Fla. . . . Eric Eberz scored 19 points to lead Villanova (6-5) 
to an 81-80 victory over Richmond (4-7) at Richmond, Va. 
</P>
