<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC SAN DIEGO HITS CHAPMAN HARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman learned about humility Tuesday night when the Panthers were soundly 
defeated by UC San Diego, 77-61, in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the Panthers (8-5) had defeated the Tritons earlier in the season, 
81-68, in the Redlands Tournament, UC San Diego (12-3), winners of 10 of its 
last 11 games, quickly took control.  
</P>
<P>
 "They were magnificent," Chapman Coach Mike Bokosky said of the Tritons. "They 
were really ready to play. They came out and controlled the tempo. They took a 
10-point lead early and we never recovered. They kept their poise, the sign of 
a real good team." 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman shot only .339 from the field, falling behind, 25-12, on Rodney 
Lusain's three-point basket at 12:02 of the first half. With Lusain hitting 18 
of his game-high 20 points in the first half from the outside, and freshman 
center Matt Aune muscling his way inside with 18 points, the Panthers could do 
little to counter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tritons took a 44-28 halftime lead on Aune's last-second basket. Chapman 
made a five-point run at the start of the second half, but UC San Diego went on 
an 11-3 run, led by Aune, for a 55-36 lead with 14:01 left to play. The 
Panthers went six minutes without scoring during the spell and never got closer 
than 14 points with 1:29 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Stefan Mumaw led Chapman with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Golden State Athletic Conference men's game: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 77, Fresno Pacific 68 -- Craig Martin had 19 points and eight 
rebounds, Timothy Morris added 13 points and Vujadin Jovic had 10 points and 
eight rebounds to lead Concordia (11-5, 1-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's play: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 75, Concordia 69 -- Gitte Mejer made 12 of 16 shots and 
finished with 26 points for visiting Concordia in the conference opener for 
both teams. Julie Workman added 24 points for Concordia. Fresno Pacific (9-5, 
1-0) made 20 of 30 free throws and Concordia was six of six. Concordia was 
called for 23 fouls and Fresno Pacific had 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 71, Azusa Pacific 48 -- Tina Demarsh scored 17 
points and had eight assists for SCC (13-3, 1-0). Jamie Zitterkopf added 14 
points and 17 rebounds. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
