<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; MARTIN, MOORPARK SIZZLE IN 2ND HALF, 85-61 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sean Martin scored 19 of his 25 points in the second half to help Moorpark 
College turn a tie game into an 85-61 Western State Conference rout Tuesday 
night at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark entered halftime tied, 27-27, before outscoring the Vaqueros (9-9), 
58-34, in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin, a guard, also handed out 10 assists for the Raiders (16-4 overall, 4-0 
in conference), who won their ninth consecutive game. WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 60, Glendale 54 -- Forward Janette Oriza had 16 points and 17 
rebounds while point guard Joy Garcia added 12 points and five assists to lead 
the host Raiders (7-10, 4-0) in the Western State Conference interdivision 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 After trailing, 26-25, at halftime, Moorpark went on an 11-2 run to open the 
second half. Glendale got back into the game with eight minutes remaining 
before getting into foul trouble. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 79, Oxnard 54 -- Rebekah Cunnan scored a career-high 30 points and 
added nine rebounds to lead Canyons (7-11, 3-1) in the Western State Conference 
inter-division game at Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Cunnan made 10 of 20 shots and 10 of 13 free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Compton 53, Valley 41 -- Nicole Baynes scored 11 points for the visiting 
Monarchs (6-14, 1-3) in the Western State Conference loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley, plagued by poor field-goal shooting, hit just 15 of 61 shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 54, Santa Monica 44 -- Julie Hardy scored a game-high 24 points and 
grabbed 13 rebounds to lead the Pirates (14-4, 4-0) past Santa Monica (5-10, 
3-1) in a Western State Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 Andrea Williams added 18 points and seven assists for Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona-Pitzer 70, Cal Lutheran 63 -- Kelli McCaskill had 19 points and 13 
rebounds in a losing effort for the Regals (4-6) in an SCIAC opener at Thousand 
Oaks. 
</P>
