WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; SUSPECT SOUGHT IN ROBBERY AT DOMINO'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura police are searching for a robbery suspect who held up a pizza 
delivery business wearing a black trench coat, pink gloves and a blue 
handkerchief tied over his face. 
</P>
<P>
 The manager of Domino's Pizza on Thompson Boulevard told police that he was 
working inside the store about 6 p.m. Monday when he heard a dog barking 
outside the rear door.When the manager opened the door to look outside, a man 
armed with a small, silver-colored revolver confronted him and gestured for the 
manager to fill a bank bag with cash. 
</P>
<P>
 After the manager complied, the robber forced him into the walk-in freezer and 
piled several items in front of the door. The manager escaped about 30 minutes 
later and flagged down a passing police officer. 
</P>
<P>
 The manager described the suspect as a white male of medium build with severe 
acne on his forehead. JULIE FIELDS 
