<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; BAR FIGHT LEAVES 1 IN HOSPITAL, 1 IN 
JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A barroom brawl in Port Hueneme left one man in the hospital in serious 
condition and another man in jail. 
</P>
<P>
 James Ellis, 23, of San Diego was arrested after Robert Bowers, 41, of Port 
Hueneme was stabbed in the neck with a broken beer bottle.The two had been 
playing pool and drinking together most of the evening, said Sgt. Jerry Beck of 
the Port Hueneme Police Department.  
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that just after midnight, Ellis attacked Bowers without 
provocation, lunging at him with a broken beer bottle.  
</P>
<P>
 Bowers was taken to St. John's Regional Medical Center, where he underwent 
surgery early Tuesday to repair nerves damaged in the attack. He is listed in 
stable condition, said a hospital spokeswoman, who added that the attack came 
close to cutting an artery. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Ellis a short distance from the bar.  
</P>
<P>
 He was covered in blood and suffering from a broken nose, Beck said. He was 
booked into county jail on suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon and 
inflicting grievous bodily harm. His bail was set at $5,000. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
