<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK: BOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Steve Aylsworth 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: Westlake 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Aylsworth, Westlake's sixth man, has been the key to the 
Warriors' strong start in the Marmonte League. Aylsworth (5-foot-11) is a 
flashy ballhandler with a deft shooting touch from three-point range.He leads 
Westlake (9-2, 3-0 in league play) with 15.6 points, 4.1 assists and 3.0 steals 
a game. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Aylsworth scored 53 points with 10 assists and seven steals 
as Westlake defeated Newbury Park, 82-79, and Thousand Oaks, 57-52. He had 21 
points, seven assists and four steals against Newbury Park -- and was even 
better against Thousand Oaks. Aylsworth scored a career-high 32 points against 
the Lancers, including 11 of Westlake's 12 points in the second quarter and 16 
of his team's 22 in the fourth quarter. "My shot felt really good," Aylsworth 
said. "I kept putting them up and they kept going in." 
</P>
