<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: DFG PLANS TO DOUBLE PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trout fishing in the city is on the upswing, thanks to the Department of Fish 
and Game's expanded Urban Lakes Program. 
</P>
<P>
 Citing a positive public response to the program it started last year, the DFG 
plans to nearly double the number of urban lakes in Los Angeles and Orange 
counties to be regularly stocked with catchable trout in 1994.  
</P>
<P>
 On the list for this year are Echo Park Lake near downtown Los Angeles, Balboa 
Park Lake in the San Fernando Valley, Alondra Park Lake in Torrance, Cerritos 
Park Lake, Kenneth Hahn Park Lake in Baldwin Hills, La Mirada Park Lake, Magic 
Lake in Willowbrook, Lincoln Park Lake in Lincoln Hills, Centennial Park Lake 
in Santa Ana and Tri-City Park Lake in Placentia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
