<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: FAITH BAPTIST'S GRANZOW 8-MAN CO-PLAYER OF YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quarterback Judd Granzow of Faith Baptist High has been named co-player of the 
year in the Southern Section's eight-man football large division. 
</P>
<P>
 Granzow, a junior who also plays basketball and baseball, led the Contenders 
to the division final. He shared the award with senior running back Brian 
Messing of Brentwood, which defeated Faith Baptist in the championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 Juniors Andre Menart (defensive line), Colby Carpenter (linebacker) and Rani 
Zahr (defensive back) also were first-team selections for the Contenders. 
</P>
<P>
 In the small schools division, defensive lineman Tom Vondra and running back 
Jimmy Barnett, seniors at Lancaster Bethel Christian, were first-team 
selections. Baseball  
</P>
<P>
 Senior left-hander Randy Wolf of El Camino Real High has been ranked among the 
nation's best high school prospects by Baseball America magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 Wolf, who led the Conquistadores to the City Section 4-A Division championship 
last spring, is ranked 45th on the national list. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley third baseman Ryan Hankins is ranked 78th, Monroe right-handed 
pitcher Joel Zamudio is ranked 81st and infielder Kirk Hagge of Crescenta 
Valley is ranked 93rd. Boxing  
</P>
<P>
 Robert Garcia of Oxnard will make his professional debut in an eight-round 
featherweight bout against James Dean of Planada, Calif., Feb. 4 at the Oxnard 
Civic Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia, 9-0 with eight knockouts as an amateur, is coming off a second-round 
knockout of Hector Diaz of Puerto Penasco, Mexico, on Sunday night in Del Mar. 
Golf  
</P>
<P>
 A pair of golfers with ties to the region pulled off a rare feat at River 
Ridge Golf Club in Oxnard on Monday when each recorded a hole in one on 
consecutive shots. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat Shanahan of Redondo Beach and Mark Munoz of Ventura, playing in the same 
threesome, aced the 146-yard par-three fifth hole on consecutive swings. Munoz, 
36, is a maintenance worker at River Ridge. Shanahan, 30, is a Buena High 
graduate who played football at Utah. College baseball  
</P>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge alumni baseball game will be held Jan. 23 at 1 p.m. 
at Matador Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-885-3233 or 885-3208. 
</P>
</TEXT>
