</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Semiconductor Book-to-Bill Ratio Goes Up: The industry ratio for the North 
American market increased in December, according to statistics collected by 
World Semiconductor Trade Statistics and released by the San Jose-based 
Semiconductor Industry Assn.December bookings in the North American market 
(orders based on a three-month moving average) were $2.276 billion -- up 3.0% 
from the $2.210 billion recorded in November -- and 20.0% higher than the 
$1.896 billion figure posted in December, 1992. The December book-to-bill ratio 
is 1.04. November's preliminary ratio remains unchanged at 0.99. A book-to-bill 
ratio of 1.04 means that for every $100 worth of products shipped (billed), 
manufacturers received $104 worth of new orders (bookings). 
</P>
</TEXT>
