<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE TRAVEL; ZAGAT SURVEY: DENVER RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Copyright 1993, Eugene H. Zagat Jr. and Nina S. Zagat 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The following reviews are excerpted from Zagat Surveys, a series of regional 
dining and lodging guides based on extensive ratings and reviews contributed by 
local restaurant-goers and frequent travelers. Ratings for food, decor and 
service are based on a numerical scale: 0-9, poor to fair; 10-19, good to very 
good; 20-25, very good to excellent; 26-30, extraordinary to perfect. Estimated 
cost is for a dinner, drink and tip for one person. 
</P>
<P>
 Zagat suggests business travelers consider these establishments when 
entertaining clients, or conducting business. Cafes 
</P>
<P>
 CITY SPIRIT CAFE 
</P>
<P>
 1434 Blake St.; (303) 575-0022 Soho meets Santa Monica at this downtown 
health-oriented restaurant with Day-Glo decor. Everyone likes the sprouts and 
avocados. Good coffee and nice at night for drinks and dessert. Food: 17 Decor: 
21 Service: 15 Cost: $12 
</P>
<P>
 DEVINE CAFE 
</P>
<P>
 2033 E. Colfax Ave.; (303) 333-8463 Nouvelle fare with Southwestern accent. 
Impressive presentations and flavors as well as a good wine list. This sleek 
eatery near Capitol Hill is also convenient for a downtown lunch.  
</P>
<P>
 Food: 21 Decor: 17 Service: 20 Cost: $18 
</P>
<P>
 EUROPEAN CAFE 
</P>
<P>
 1515 Market St.; (303) 825-6555 Downtown Denver branch of a popular Boulder 
restaurant is among town's favorites, with incredible sauces and dressings 
throughout an extensive, generally French-American menu. Some find it stuffy.  
</P>
<P>
 Food: 26 Decor: 25 Service: 24 Cost: $30 
</P>
<P>
 LITTLE RUSSIAN CAFE 
</P>
<P>
 Larimer Square; (303) 595-8600 So corny it's good, this restaurant serves 
authentic, hearty peasant food. You can wash it down with vodka from a large 
selection.  
</P>
<P>
 Food: 20 Decor: 20 Service: 19 Cost: $19 Hotel Dining 
</P>
<P>
 AUGUSTA 
</P>
<P>
 Westin Hotel, 1672 Lawrence St . ; (303) 572-7222 Posh, romantic and opulent, 
this continental-style restaurant is popular for Valentine's Day. Pretty room 
has floor-to-ceiling views of lower downtown. Pastas and desserts get raves.  
</P>
<P>
 Food: 24 Decor: 27 Service: 25 Cost: $32 
</P>
<P>
 PALACE ARMS 
</P>
<P>
 Brown Palace Hotel, 321 17th St.; (303) 297-3111 The grande dame of hotel 
dining rooms is consistently good, with elegant service and one of the best 
wine lists in town.  
</P>
<P>
 Food: 26 Decor: 28 Service: 26 Cost: $35 
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to participate in future surveys, call (800) 333-3421. 
