<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: PROFITS OF COMPUTER PRINTER MAKER DROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Printronix Inc.: The Irvine maker of computer printers posted a 46% decline in 
profit for the latest quarter.The company said it earned $325,000, or 10 cents 
a share, for its third quarter, which ended Dec. 24. That compared to a profit 
of $603,000, or 19 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier. Sales 
increased 18% to $28.2 million from $23.8 million. For the first nine months of 
its fiscal year, the company reported a profit of $952,000, or 29 cents a 
share, contrasted with a loss of $3.2 million, or $1.03 a share, for the 
corresponding period a year earlier. Nine-month sales gained 9% to $76.9 
million from $70.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
