<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Summa Industries: The Fullerton industrial equipment manufacturer, formerly 
Morehouse Industries, reported a quarterly profit of $231,000, or 15 cents a 
share, which included an extraordinary gain of $100,000 from an accounting 
change.That compared to earnings of $143,000, or 14 cents a share, for the same 
period a year earlier. Sales for the company's first fiscal quarter, which 
ended Nov. 30, rose 57% to $3.3 million from $2.1 million. The company said the 
sales increase was primarily because of a subsidiary acquired July 30. 
</P>
