<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: HEALTH; FHP PUTS LOGO ON CENTER ICE AT DUCKS GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James M. Gomez / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FHP International Corp.'s latest marketing effort is on ice. 
</P>
<P>
 The health maintenance organization, based in Fountain Valley, hopes that by 
advertising at the newly built Anaheim Arena, it can warm up to potential 
customers for its fast-growing medical services. 
</P>
<P>
 Two months ago, the company began touting itself by displaying its distinctive 
blue logo on center ice at the arena, home of the NHL's expansion hockey team, 
the Mighty Ducks. 
</P>
<P>
 FHP spokesman Eric Morely said the company signed a three-year contract with 
Walt Disney Co., owner of the Mighty Ducks, four months ago for an undisclosed 
sum. The ad is seen every time the hockey players skate past the center of the 
arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Other perks include having FHP's name in programs and on a new marquee to be 
erected at the end of the month. The kicker will be on Jan. 24, when hockey 
fans will receive hockey pucks with FHP's logo engraved on them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
