<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; MAN ESCAPES SERIOUS INJURY IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A "very lucky" 18-year-old Pacoima man escaped serious injury Monday when a 
bullet lodged between his skull and forehead during an assault, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Francisco Javier Beltran Martinez was shot once by an unknown gunman Monday as 
he pulled his car into a driveway, said Sgt. Joe Flores of the Los Angeles 
Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 "Several rounds were fired at the victim at close range, but only one bullet 
hit him in the forehead, and it didn't penetrate the skull," Flores said. 
</P>
<P>
 The attack occurred as the victim stepped from his car on Adelphia Avenue 
shortly after 6 p.m., Flores said. 
</P>
<P>
 Flores and an unidentified official at Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission 
Hills described the victim as a very lucky man. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center where he was treated for a 
single gunshot wound. He was released Monday night, a hospital spokeswoman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have no motive for the shooting and no one has been arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's not a clear-cut case like a gang shooting," Flores said. CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
