council's Budget and Finance Committee. Manning's report calls for, among other 
things, restoration of $487,000 to the Fire Department's budget to help inspect 
properties for brush clearance requirements, $1.35 million to provide emergency 
training for firefighters and $9.8 million to replace antiquated equipment. 
