<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; HOUSE, GARAGE FIRE MAY HAVE BEEN SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A vacant house and detached garage suffered about $80,000 in damage during a 
fire Tuesday morning that may have been deliberately set, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire was spotted raging through a single-story, three-bedroom house in the 
1400 block of West Richland Avenue at 11:40 a.m., said Santa Ana Deputy Fire 
Chief Wayne Bowman. 
</P>
<P>
 "The origin of the fire was suspicious," Bowman said. "We had some witnesses 
who said they saw people leaving the house right before the fire." 
</P>
<P>
 It took 16 firefighters about 28 minutes to put out the blaze, which did not 
damage any other homes on the street. 
</P>
<P>
 Bowman said the house was basically empty except for some discarded clothing. 
He said a family that lived in the house had recently been evicted. 
</P>
<P>
 "The eviction and the fire do not appear to be related," Bowman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
