<HEADLINE>
<P>
COACH QUITS AFTER DISMAL TENURE; HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL: KNIGHT GIVES UP AFTER 
GOING 1-29 IN THREE SEASONS AT HUENEME HIGH, CLAIMS LACK OF SUPPORT. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON H. REID, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citing lack of support for the football program from the Hueneme High 
administration, Coach Ed Knight resigned Tuesday after three dismal seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was just a horrible time commitment," Knight said."There was only one 
other coach besides myself who was also on the teaching staff and there was no 
change in sight. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just didn't feel I could do a good enough job in so many different areas 
without more help." 
</P>
<P>
 School administrators confirmed Knight's resignation but would not comment on 
his reasons for leaving. 
</P>
<P>
 Knight, 54, said he will remain a teacher at Hueneme. He would not comment on 
whether he is pursuing another coaching position. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vikings were 1-29 in three years under Knight, including 0-21 in Channel 
League play. Hueneme's only victory during the Knight regime was over Channel 
Islands early this season, which snapped a 21-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
 A major problem for Knight throughout his tenure was his inability to attract 
players to the program. The Vikings had only 28 players on the team this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 Reaction to Knight's decision was mixed. Some players said Knight was 
uncommunicative. 
</P>
<P>
 "I had problems with him," junior offensive lineman Joe Moreno said. "He never 
really had good communication with his players. I'm not going to miss him." 
</P>
<P>
 Others, however, praised Knight for his effort under difficult circumstances. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought he was a pretty good coach," sophomore defensive lineman Orlando 
Carrillo said. "I always thought he tried to bring out the best in us." 
</P>
<P>
 Knight said he has no regrets about how he handled his team. 
</P>
<P>
 "All coaches have problems communicating with their players at times," Knight 
said. "I don't think I had a lot of those problems, but everybody has their own 
interpretation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
